document_data.mainbody:
'''Amhar''' was a [[dwarf]] who served as a royal guardsmen of [[Tethyr]] in the late 15{{th}} century [[DR]]. He was dismissed when he was convicted as perpetrator of the [[Children's Massacre]] in [[1469 DR]], called the Scourge of Tethyr and the Killer of Children and hated throughout all of Tethyr. In his middle years, he traveled with [[Harp (captain)|Harp]], captain of the ship ''[[Crane]]'', around [[1479 DR]].
{{Quote
|You're Amhar, the infamous killer of children. Honestly, I don't know how I missed it.
|Harp
}}
